There is nothing to be ashamed of
Widely used in Zen, but source unknown.

>Shogen Yamakawa, abbot of Shogenji Temple and master of the Shogen Monastery
>It is an old saying, "If you sit for an inch, you will become a Buddha for an inch. The time it takes for a stick of incense to burn out is called "issun-no jikan. It is usually about five minutes or ten minutes. If you do this well, even if it is only for a short time, you will be able to say, "If you sit for an inch, you will become a Buddha for an inch.
